      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Your kids see themselves drained, not you, and they're carrying that weight too - not just physically with caregiving, but also emotionally and mentally. Their tired and stressed faces are because of the accumulated stress of supporting you, not because they think of you solely as a problem. It's a vicious cycle where you're suffocating everyone's efforts to recharge and rebuild. Accept that this season is unsustainable, and maybe it's time to have an honest conversation with your husband about delegating more responsibilities or seeking external support to break the cycle.",
      "source": "target",
